        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The `vim.pack` does not do full clone, it does [so called blobless clone](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/ce9a73625ab1700b0dc9efbacf10629c9e222ccd/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua#L181). This is the best compromise when it comes to reducing cloned repo size while not introducing problems later with checkouts and/or updates.\n\nShallow clones fully truncate history and related blobs which means that there need to be extra steps when it comes to resolving `version`. Like if there is no match for a `version = 'v0.1.0'`, is it because of the shallow clone history truncation or user specified an incorrect tag? The blobless clone already contains all necessary Git information and allows answering this question.\n\nThe current approach is what most of plugin managers use and it is a more \"battle tested\" approach. So I think this is safe to close as not planned.",
